      <hedline>
        <hl1>Not Best vs. Best</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>There is now at least a 50-50 chance that the next World Series champion will be the ninth-best team in America.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>There is now at least a 50-50 chance that the next World Series champion will be the ninth-best team in America.</p>
        <p>The Yankees' .540 winning percentage in the regular season was surpassed by eight other clubs.</p>
        <p>The playoff structure has been dramatic and entertaining and produced the result that will send television executives into cartwheels, an all-New York Series. But it did not produce what the original World Series had produced for decades, a clash of the best team in the American League against the best team in the National League.</p>
        <p>Now the best we can hope for is that America's fifth-best team, the Mets, will win.</p>
        <p>JOHN B. HOLWAY  Springfield, Va.</p>
      </block>
